Think what you want.

00:08:05.527 --> 00:08:11.491 position:50% align:center
Believe them, or not.
I don't care.

00:08:11.533 --> 00:08:15.704 position:50% align:center
My parents didn't
believe me. No one did.

00:08:15.745 --> 00:08:19.916 position:50% align:center
I'm done trying
to convince people.

00:08:19.958 --> 00:08:22.419 position:50% align:center
What's the point?

00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:25.755 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Machi, do you hate
when things are in order?

00:08:25.797 --> 00:08:27.549 position:50% align:center
[MACHI gasps]

00:08:27.590 --> 00:08:29.426 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
A pristine snowfall.

00:08:29.467 --> 00:08:31.094 position:50% align:center
A neat and tidy room.

00:08:31.136 --> 00:08:35.432 position:50% align:center
Anything that seems
perfect bothers you.

00:08:36.641 --> 00:08:38.852 position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:08:38.893 --> 00:08:43.857 position:50% align:center
Yes. It... scares me.

00:08:43.898 --> 00:08:47.944 position:50% align:center
You have to be perfect.
Do you understand me?

00:08:47.986 --> 00:08:51.698 position:50% align:center
Your personality,
your grades. Everything!

00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:55.994 position:50% align:center
Otherwise, you will never
beat that woman's son.

00:08:56.036 --> 00:09:00.081 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
My whole life, I was so nervous.

00:09:01.458 --> 00:09:05.420 position:50% align:center
[MACHI] The tiniest misstep
and she'd be furious.

00:09:05.462 --> 00:09:10.633 position:50% align:center
Like I was walking a tightrope
that grew thinner every day.

00:09:10.675 --> 00:09:16.348 position:50% align:center
Perfection is terrifying.
Suffocating.

00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:19.142 position:50% align:center
I can't stand it.

00:09:19.184 --> 00:09:20.769 position:50% align:center
I tried, though.

00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:24.272 position:50% align:center
I did my best to be what
they wanted me to be.

00:09:24.314 --> 00:09:26.274 position:50% align:center
But...

00:09:26.316 --> 00:09:31.571 position:50% align:center
But now, there's my
little brother, so I--

00:09:31.613 --> 00:09:33.239 position:50% align:center
[MACHI'S MOTHER]
It's wonderful.

00:09:33.281 --> 00:09:36.368 position:50% align:center
We finally got the boy
we were hoping for!

00:09:36.409 --> 00:09:39.120 position:50% align:center
This will be so much
better for everyone.

00:09:39.162 --> 00:09:42.665 position:50% align:center
I mean, there's Machi,
but she's just so... plain.

00:09:42.707 --> 00:09:46.711 position:50% align:center
Really, it's like the girl
has no personality at all.

00:09:46.753 --> 00:09:48.797 position:50% align:center
She's so boring.

00:09:48.838 --> 00:09:52.384 position:50% align:center
I guess good grades
aren't everything, are they?

00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:54.177 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
What?

00:09:54.219 --> 00:09:57.097 position:50% align:center
Why would you say
something like that?

00:09:57.138 --> 00:09:59.683 position:50% align:center
You think I'm boring?

00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:02.602 position:50% align:center
I did everything you
told me to, though.

00:10:02.644 --> 00:10:07.357 position:50% align:center
I worked hard to be
perfect, like you said.

00:10:07.399 --> 00:10:10.276 position:50% align:center
So it's my fault you
turned out this way?

00:10:10.318 --> 00:10:14.030 position:50% align:center
You're laying your
failures at my feet?

00:10:14.072 --> 00:10:18.952 position:50% align:center
Well, fine. I suppose I do
share some of the blame.

00:10:18.993 --> 00:10:24.207 position:50% align:center
I did raise you. Clearly,
I went wrong somewhere.

00:10:25.542 --> 00:10:31.172 position:50% align:center
[MACHI] No. That's not
what I needed you to say.

00:10:31.214 --> 00:10:35.844 position:50% align:center
I did everything I could,
and this is what you tell me?

00:10:35.885 --> 00:10:39.764 position:50% align:center
I'm something that went wrong.

00:10:39.806 --> 00:10:43.476 position:50% align:center
If I'm a mistake,
what do I do now?

00:10:47.522 --> 00:10:51.192 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
Where... do I go from here?

00:10:52.569 --> 00:10:55.530 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
You've worked hard, right?

00:10:57.741 --> 00:11:00.869 position:50% align:center
You have. I can tell you have.

00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:04.664 position:50% align:center
You worked hard to become
the person you are, and...

00:11:04.706 --> 00:11:06.499 position:50% align:center
...I'm glad.

00:11:09.711 --> 00:11:11.379 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
You did well.

00:11:13.048 --> 00:11:18.386 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
Somebody thinks... I did well.

00:11:18.428 --> 00:11:22.057 position:50% align:center
I never imagined
I would hear that.

00:11:22.098 --> 00:11:25.143 position:50% align:center
Not once.

00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:28.688 position:50% align:center
My whole life,
I've been a screw-up.

00:11:28.730 --> 00:11:32.692 position:50% align:center
A mistake. Something
that went wrong.

00:11:32.734 --> 00:11:38.448 position:50% align:center
But... he thinks I did well.

00:11:40.867 --> 00:11:44.412 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
It was cold.

00:11:44.454 --> 00:11:48.291 position:50% align:center
And I was worried
about my brother.

00:11:48.333 --> 00:11:54.047 position:50% align:center
I just... didn't want him
to get sick, you know?

00:11:54.089 --> 00:11:58.093 position:50% align:center
So I went to cover
him with a blanket.

00:11:58.134 --> 00:11:59.511 position:50% align:center
[MACHI'S MOTHER]
What are you doing?

00:11:59.552 --> 00:12:02.013 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
I wasn't trying to hurt him.

00:12:05.266 --> 00:12:05.934 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
But they...

00:12:05.975 --> 00:12:07.352 position:50% align:center
I don't want to hear it!

00:12:07.394 --> 00:12:09.938 position:50% align:center
I've worried this
might be the case.

00:12:09.979 --> 00:12:12.774 position:50% align:center
[MACHI] I couldn't get
them to understand.

00:12:12.816 --> 00:12:17.612 position:50% align:center
I tried, but they'd already
made up their minds.

00:12:17.654 --> 00:12:22.075 position:50% align:center
I just wanted...
to keep him warm.

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:33.878 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Hey, if this
snow keeps piling up...

00:12:35.672 --> 00:12:39.092 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] ...we'll make
footprints in it. Together.

00:12:45.348 --> 00:12:46.975 position:50% align:center
Promise.

00:12:49.102 --> 00:12:49.978 position:50% align:center
--[phone rings]
--[BOTH gasp]

00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:51.855 position:50% align:center
[MANABE yells]

00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:54.399 position:50% align:center
Sorry! My stupid phone!

00:12:54.441 --> 00:12:55.608 position:50% align:center
Shoulda put it on silent.

00:12:55.650 --> 00:12:58.111 position:50% align:center
You were totally about
to kiss, weren't you?

00:12:58.153 --> 00:12:59.821 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
Shut up, you idiot!

00:12:59.863 --> 00:13:02.741 position:50% align:center
[MANABE]
Okay, it's on vibrate now!

00:13:02.782 --> 00:13:05.160 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
The snow didn't stick, though.

00:13:05.201 --> 00:13:08.079 position:50% align:center
It melted overnight.

00:13:08.121 --> 00:13:11.416 position:50% align:center
And by morning, it was gone.

00:13:12.834 --> 00:13:15.545 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Any other opinions?

00:13:15.587 --> 00:13:17.047 position:50% align:center
Well, sounds like
we've got that settled...

00:13:17.088 --> 00:13:18.798 position:50% align:center
Got you something.

00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:20.842 position:50% align:center
Here. It's a brand-new box.

00:13:20.884 --> 00:13:24.971 position:50% align:center
Aw! That is so sweet. Thank you!

00:13:25.013 --> 00:13:28.224 position:50% align:center
Kimi isn't on chalkboard
duty today, though.

00:13:28.266 --> 00:13:30.810 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT C]
Oh, my bad.

00:13:30.852 --> 00:13:31.978 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:32.020 --> 00:13:34.981 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] ...to make sure
everything goes smoothly.

00:13:35.023 --> 00:13:38.526 position:50% align:center
Next up, regarding club
activities for spring break,

00:13:38.568 --> 00:13:40.570 position:50% align:center
there's been a slight change.

00:13:40.612 --> 00:13:42.489 position:50% align:center
The hard end time
was originally 6 PM...

00:13:42.530 --> 00:13:46.951 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
It's gone now, but I wonder...

00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:49.996 position:50% align:center
...will he remember
what he said?

00:13:50.038 --> 00:13:52.624 position:50% align:center
Will he make footprints with me?

00:13:54.376 --> 00:13:57.587 position:50% align:center
[MACHI]
I hope it snows soon.

00:13:57.629 --> 00:14:02.884 position:50% align:center
It's hard to believe, but for
the first time in my life,

00:14:02.926 --> 00:14:05.095 position:50% align:center
I'm wishing for snow.

00:14:06.513 --> 00:14:10.266 position:50% align:center
Okay. Here! Uh, Kyo?

00:14:10.308 --> 00:14:14.145 position:50% align:center
Um. Right. Thank you.

00:14:15.563 --> 00:14:17.816 position:50% align:center
[UOTANI] It's pretty crazy
to think that we've only got

00:14:17.857 --> 00:14:20.485 position:50% align:center
one year left as high
schoolers, isn't it?

00:14:20.527 --> 00:14:23.071 position:50% align:center
The passage of time
is a curious thing.

00:14:23.113 --> 00:14:24.989 position:50% align:center
We could use some
help over here!

00:14:25.031 --> 00:14:26.574 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah? Tough.

00:14:26.616 --> 00:14:29.494 position:50% align:center
You wouldn't even have any
flowers if it wasn't for us.

00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:31.913 position:50% align:center
Hey, it's not like I asked
those girls to run off with 'em!

00:14:31.955 --> 00:14:32.956 position:50% align:center
[KYO yelps]

00:14:32.997 --> 00:14:34.749 position:50% align:center
Uh! Watch out!

00:14:34.791 --> 00:14:36.501 position:50% align:center
Tohru!

00:14:36.543 --> 00:14:38.294 position:50% align:center
[KYO grunts]

00:14:38.336 --> 00:14:39.254 position:50% align:center
Are you okay?

00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:41.131 position:50% align:center
Uh. Yeah, thanks.

00:14:41.172 --> 00:14:42.424 position:50% align:center
You jerk.

00:14:42.465 --> 00:14:45.051 position:50% align:center
Kyon. Tohru almost got hurt.

00:14:45.093 --> 00:14:47.137 position:50% align:center
That's not something
we can forgive.

00:14:47.178 --> 00:14:49.723 position:50% align:center
[KYO] You were the
ones who started it!

00:14:49.764 --> 00:14:53.184 position:50% align:center
Well, just checking in.
I should get going now.

00:14:53.226 --> 00:14:56.354 position:50% align:center
Right. I guess you need to
get back to student council.

00:14:56.396 --> 00:14:59.524 position:50% align:center
No. I'm meeting up with
someone, actually.

00:14:59.566 --> 00:15:00.734 position:50% align:center
Hm?

00:15:02.819 --> 00:15:05.030 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
Once I graduate,

00:15:05.071 --> 00:15:09.534 position:50% align:center
there will be no place for me
at this school anymore.

00:15:09.576 --> 00:15:14.998 position:50% align:center
The familiar hallways,
the lockers, the classrooms.

00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:17.917 position:50% align:center
They'll belong to other people.

00:15:17.959 --> 00:15:21.129 position:50% align:center
That's what graduation means.

00:15:21.171 --> 00:15:25.592 position:50% align:center
Moving on. Saying goodbye.

00:15:25.633 --> 00:15:27.177 position:50% align:center
But...

00:15:28.261 --> 00:15:30.722 position:50% align:center
[YUKI] Sorry. Hope you
weren't waiting long.

00:15:30.764 --> 00:15:35.226 position:50% align:center
Oh, no, it's fine!
I'm just happy that you came.

00:15:35.268 --> 00:15:37.771 position:50% align:center
So I'll get right to it, then.

00:15:37.812 --> 00:15:40.273 position:50% align:center
Or... that's what
I intended to do,

00:15:40.315 --> 00:15:44.819 position:50% align:center
but suddenly, my mind seems to
have gone completely blank.

00:15:44.861 --> 00:15:48.698 position:50% align:center
Sorry. How silly of me.

00:15:48.740 --> 00:15:51.368 position:50% align:center
Right. Here goes.

00:15:51.409 --> 00:15:56.247 position:50% align:center
I wanted to say I'm glad
I met you. Really glad.

00:15:56.289 --> 00:16:01.336 position:50% align:center
I was lucky, coming to a high
school as special as this one.

00:16:01.378 --> 00:16:05.507 position:50% align:center
Every day was a new adventure,
like a never-ending festival.

00:16:05.548 --> 00:16:11.721 position:50% align:center
I laughed. I cried. Caused
more than a little trouble.

00:16:11.763 --> 00:16:17.143 position:50% align:center
And at the center of
it all, there was you.

00:16:17.185 --> 00:16:19.813 position:50% align:center
I loved you.

00:16:19.854 --> 00:16:22.607 position:50% align:center
I loved you, Yuki.

00:16:22.649 --> 00:16:26.945 position:50% align:center
So, I guess what I'm
trying to say is...

00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:30.115 position:50% align:center
...I want the best for you.

00:16:30.156 --> 00:16:34.744 position:50% align:center
I hope that, whatever comes,
whatever the future holds,

00:16:34.786 --> 00:16:37.789 position:50% align:center
you'll find happiness, too.

00:16:37.831 --> 00:16:41.084 position:50% align:center
And if you've already found it,
if you're already happy,

00:16:41.126 --> 00:16:45.630 position:50% align:center
then I hope there's even greater
happiness in store for you.

00:16:45.672 --> 00:16:48.425 position:50% align:center
I've had my own
taste of happiness.

00:16:48.466 --> 00:16:53.722 position:50% align:center
The years I spent here, that
was a gift. A precious gift.

00:16:53.763 --> 00:16:56.057 position:50% align:center
One you gave me.

00:16:56.099 --> 00:16:58.560 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry, but this
is the only way

00:16:58.601 --> 00:17:01.354 position:50% align:center
I can think of to pay you back.

00:17:03.690 --> 00:17:05.358 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
Thank you.

00:17:06.735 --> 00:17:10.905 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
Please... let him understand.

00:17:10.947 --> 00:17:14.159 position:50% align:center
I'm not doing this to get
anything from him.

00:17:14.200 --> 00:17:17.662 position:50% align:center
I don't expect him to
return my feelings.

00:17:19.039 --> 00:17:23.710 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]I just want him
to know that I was happy.

00:17:23.752 --> 00:17:30.050 position:50% align:center
I had so much fun here, and I'm
truly glad to have met him.

00:17:30.091 --> 00:17:32.135 position:50% align:center
So please...

00:17:34.179 --> 00:17:37.349 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
...let him understand.

00:17:37.390 --> 00:17:39.351 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO gasps]

00:17:39.392 --> 00:17:40.894 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
To be honest,

00:17:40.935 --> 00:17:44.606 position:50% align:center
I think that's more
than I deserve, but...

00:17:44.647 --> 00:17:45.440 position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:17:45.482 --> 00:17:46.733 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:47.859 --> 00:17:53.239 position:50% align:center
Yes. Thank you very much.

00:17:57.077 --> 00:17:57.827 position:50% align:center
[YUKI]
Still, I'm--

00:17:57.869 --> 00:18:01.664 position:50% align:center
Ah! Please, just stop
right there, Yuki!

00:18:01.706 --> 00:18:02.791 position:50% align:center
Really.

00:18:02.832 --> 00:18:05.919 position:50% align:center
Surprisingly, I find I'm feeling
quite good at the moment.

00:18:05.960 --> 00:18:09.005 position:50% align:center
I'd hate for you to ruin it
with an ill-timed apology.

00:18:09.047 --> 00:18:11.508 position:50% align:center
You don't want me
to cry, do you?

00:18:11.549 --> 00:18:14.636 position:50% align:center
Besides, don't discount karma.

00:18:14.678 --> 00:18:16.805 position:50% align:center
These things might be
fairer than we think.

00:18:16.846 --> 00:18:18.473 position:50% align:center
For all we know,
somebody may have been

00:18:18.515 --> 00:18:20.892 position:50% align:center
pining desperately for
me all along, as well.

00:18:20.934 --> 00:18:22.769 position:50% align:center
Like former president Takei?

00:18:22.811 --> 00:18:24.562 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
No. Absolutely not!

00:18:24.604 --> 00:18:25.647 position:50% align:center
[YUKI chuckles]

00:18:25.689 --> 00:18:26.981 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO sighs]

00:18:27.023 --> 00:18:30.402 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
Honestly, Yuki, you're so...

00:18:31.152 --> 00:18:35.490 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO crying]

00:18:35.532 --> 00:18:37.283 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
Thank you.

00:18:50.880 --> 00:18:57.554 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS] ♪ The kindness
shown from mentors dear ♪

00:18:57.595 --> 00:19:04.144 position:50% align:center
♪ has brought us
to this year. ♪

00:19:04.185 --> 00:19:10.775 position:50% align:center
♪ The time we've shared
has come and gone ♪

00:19:10.817 --> 00:19:17.407 position:50% align:center
♪ as quickly as the dawn. ♪

00:19:17.449 --> 00:19:23.997 position:50% align:center
♪ The days turned into
months and years ♪

00:19:24.039 --> 00:19:30.628 position:50% align:center
♪ and now we're
finally here. ♪

00:19:30.670 --> 00:19:38.928 position:50% align:center
♪ Our time to learn
has passed us by ♪

00:19:38.970 --> 00:19:46.227 position:50% align:center
♪ and now we say goodbye. ♪

00:19:48.813 --> 00:19:52.150 position:50% align:center
[NAOHITO]
So, sad to be leaving?

00:19:52.192 --> 00:19:55.945 position:50% align:center
Oh, goodness, you caught me.
How embarrassing.

00:19:55.987 --> 00:19:59.240 position:50% align:center
I wanted to take one last
little look at the classroom.

00:19:59.282 --> 00:20:00.867 position:50% align:center
But I'm done now.

00:20:02.035 --> 00:20:04.871 position:50% align:center
[NAOHITO]
Mi-Minagawa-<i>senpai</i>!

00:20:04.913 --> 00:20:07.707 position:50% align:center
The thing is... I...

00:20:07.749 --> 00:20:11.127 position:50% align:center
Well, I just...

00:20:11.169 --> 00:20:15.882 position:50% align:center
I-I always... thought... Um...

00:20:19.719 --> 00:20:22.764 position:50% align:center
After "goodbye" comes "hello"!

00:20:22.806 --> 00:20:27.185 position:50% align:center
All new beginnings
come from endings.

00:20:27.227 --> 00:20:33.858 position:50% align:center
So, I hope whatever the future
holds for you after graduation,

00:20:33.900 --> 00:20:37.320 position:50% align:center
you'll be happy, and...

00:20:37.362 --> 00:20:39.531 position:50% align:center
...you'll keep smiling.

00:20:41.032 --> 00:20:44.160 position:50% align:center
[MOTOKO]
Sakuragi, you, too.

00:20:44.202 --> 00:20:46.788 position:50% align:center
I hope you'll be happy.

00:20:46.830 --> 00:20:48.748 position:50% align:center
And thank you.

00:20:54.212 --> 00:20:55.672 position:50% align:center
[NAOHITO]
Goodbye.

00:21:01.344 --> 00:21:03.054 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Nice to meet you.

00:21:04.431 --> 00:21:06.808 position:50% align:center
Hiro, your name means
"a light on the path,"

00:21:06.850 --> 00:21:10.228 position:50% align:center
so I named her Hinata,
for "sunshine."

00:21:10.270 --> 00:21:11.730 position:50% align:center
Cute, right?

00:21:11.771 --> 00:21:14.357 position:50% align:center
Hinata, this is
your big brother!

00:21:14.399 --> 00:21:17.152 position:50% align:center
He's going to be starting
middle school so.

00:21:17.193 --> 00:21:18.445 position:50% align:center
Well, come on.

00:21:18.486 --> 00:21:21.781 position:50% align:center
Don't you want to hug her?
Don't be shy now.

00:21:21.823 --> 00:21:26.453 position:50% align:center
No, that's a terrible idea!
Mom, Hinata's a girl. I can't.

00:21:26.494 --> 00:21:28.121 position:50% align:center
Oh, please, it's fine.

00:21:28.163 --> 00:21:31.332 position:50% align:center
Mama's here. I can
hug you both easily.

00:21:33.418 --> 00:21:35.253 position:50% align:center
[KAGURA]
So it turns out,

00:21:35.295 --> 00:21:39.007 position:50% align:center
Isuzu graduated while she
was still in the hospital.

00:21:39.049 --> 00:21:40.216 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Good for her.

00:21:40.258 --> 00:21:43.970 position:50% align:center
And you were kind enough
to go pick up her diploma.

00:21:44.012 --> 00:21:46.264 position:50% align:center
You're such a
sweetheart, Kagura.

00:21:46.306 --> 00:21:48.725 position:50% align:center
Compliments are
meaningless from you.

00:21:48.767 --> 00:21:50.226 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:21:50.268 --> 00:21:52.020 position:50% align:center
[KAGURA]
Hey.

00:21:52.062 --> 00:21:56.274 position:50% align:center
Is that really where
she is, the hospital?

00:21:56.316 --> 00:21:58.443 position:50% align:center
Yes. That's what I'm told.

00:21:58.485 --> 00:22:01.488 position:50% align:center
[KAGURA]
Okay, but nobody seems to know

00:22:01.529 --> 00:22:04.032 position:50% align:center
which one she was admitted to.

00:22:04.074 --> 00:22:05.033 position:50% align:center
And her phone--

00:22:05.075 --> 00:22:06.117 position:50% align:center
[SHIGURE]
Now, Kagura,

00:22:06.159 --> 00:22:08.161 position:50% align:center
have you asked your
mother's advice on this?

00:22:08.203 --> 00:22:10.955 position:50% align:center
I bet she told you not to snoop.

00:22:10.997 --> 00:22:12.916 position:50% align:center
Yes, I'm snooping.

00:22:12.957 --> 00:22:15.502 position:50% align:center
This time it's just...

00:22:15.543 --> 00:22:20.632 position:50% align:center
I get the feeling that she
might not be coming back.

00:22:20.674 --> 00:22:24.010 position:50% align:center
And... I'm worried.

00:23:57.479 --> 00:24:00.398 position:50% align:center
[ISUZU]
"I'm home."